      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gay, Proud, Canadian</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stanley Hersh letter responds to July 3 news article; finds fairness and tolerance inherent in Canada's attitude toward gays are in direct contrast to entrenched homophobia in US (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The fairness and tolerance inherent in Canada's attitude toward gays (news article, July 3), as evidenced by legally recognized same-sex unions and acceptance of gays in the military and the scouts movement,  are in direct contrast to the entrenched homophobia in this country.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The fairness and tolerance inherent in Canada's attitude toward gays (news article, July 3), as evidenced by legally recognized same-sex unions and acceptance of gays in the military and the scouts movement,  are in direct contrast to the entrenched homophobia in this country.</p>
        <p>One shudders to think how the Supreme Court's ruling that the Boy Scouts of America have a right to exclude gays will jibe with the identification of the gay gene from the human genome project one day. One foresees another ridiculous confrontation between science and religion, as with evolution and creationism.</p>
        <p>STANLEY HERSH  New York, July 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
